Wrapper class: A wrapper class in Java is a class whose objects encapsulate a primitive data type (like int, boolean, or char) to allow the primitive value to be represented as an object.

The Eight Wrapper Classes :
Each of the eight primitive data types in Java has a corresponding immutable wrapper class in the java.lang package:

Primitive Data Type 	  Wrapper Class
  boolean               	Boolean
  byte	                 Byte
  char	                  Character
  short	                  Short
  int	                    Integer
  long	                  Long
  float                 	Float
  double                 	Double

